		<center>
		<p>Kharkov (Ukrainian Harkiv) - the second most populous city in Ukraine, 
		the country's scientific center, the center of the Kharkiv region.<br>
		The modern city was founded in 1654 on the site of an ancient settlement 
		identified sometimes as a Polovtsian town of the XI century Sharukan.</p>
